At first, i thought this was an issue related to limit cause limit cause default limit is 10 and this still might be the case just changing the query limit to something higher like 1000 that max. But the biggest issue this line here
```{% set hubdb_row = hubdb_table_row(hubdb_table.id, row_id) %}```
I cant seem to find where i read it but the row field can only be called a max 10 times. I rewrote the code. This should work for you.
```
{# Table Macros #}
{% set hubdb_table = hubdb_table(module.hubdb_tables.choose_table) %} {# Selects the table #}
{% set column_count = hubdb_table.columns|length %} {# Number of columns in the table #}
{% set skipped_column_count = column_count - 1 %} {# Skip first column (Name) #}

{# Fetch all rows at once for batching #}
{% set rows = hubdb_table_rows(hubdb_table.id) %}

{# Sorting based on user selection #}
{% if module.hubdb_tables.sort_rows == 'most_recent' %}
    {% set sorted_rows = rows %}
{% elif module.hubdb_tables.sort_rows == 'oldest' %}
    {% set sorted_rows = rows|reverse %}
{% else %}
    {% set sorted_rows = rows %} {# Default to no sorting #}
{% endif %}

{# HTML Starts #}
<div class="tabledb-wrapper_{{ name }}">
<div class="tabledb-container_{{ name }}" role="table" aria-label="">
  <div class="tabledb_{{ name }} headertb firstrow" role="rowgroup">
    {% for i in range(1, column_count) %} {# Loop through columns, skipping the first column #}
      {% set column_info = hubdb_table.columns[i] %}
      <div class="rowdb_{{ name }}{% if loop.first %} sticky {% endif %}" role="columnheader">{{ column_info.label }}</div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% for row in sorted_rows[:20] %} {# Process up to 20 rows #}
    <div class="tabledb_{{ name }} rowdb_{{ name }}" role="rowgroup">
      {% for i in range(1, column_count) %} {# Loop through columns, skipping the first column #}
        {% set column_info = hubdb_table.columns[i] %}
        {% set value = row[column_info.name] %}
        <div class="rowdb_{{ name }}{% if loop.first %} sticky {% endif %}" role="cell">{{ value }}</div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
</div>```
